result.execSummary:
Dale J. Graff III was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Dale J. Graff III was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Case called at 3:36 PM.
Defendant Dale J. Graff in court, in custody.  Katherine M. Findley appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
DA Findley serves defendant with a copy of fugitive warrant, complaint and affidavit.
Court informs defendant of his right to counsel.
Defendant wishes to waive extradition and counsel.
Court questions defendant re: his waiver
Court finds waiver is made freely, knowingly and intelligently.
Court signs and enters order.
